# Everything CLI (`es.exe`) ‚Äî token-aware filename search (primary Windows dev PC)

## Platform

- **`es.exe`** exists on **Windows** only (Voidtools Everything). The operator‚Äôs **L-series** workstation is the normal place to run **`.\scripts\es-find.ps1`**.
- **`lab-op`** in docs means **Linux over SSH** ‚Äî there is **no** Everything/`es` there. For filename search on the server, use **`find`**, **`fd`**, or **`locate`**, or rely on **`lab-op.ps1`** / host reports. Do **not** tell the operator to run `es.exe` **on** lab-op.

## When to use

- **Use `.\scripts\es-find.ps1`** when the task is **find files by name or path** across a **large tree**, **outside the repo**, or when **Cursor `Glob` would be huge or slow**, and you need **fast** results from the **Everything index**.
- **On Windows primary dev PC, `es.exe` is the default tool** for **filename/path** discovery (via the wrapper). **Always invoke `es-find.ps1` first** when the task is ‚Äúwhere is this file named like X‚Äù ‚Äî not **`SemanticSearch`** and not broad content **Grep** as a stand-in for filename search.
- **Prefer repo tools first** for normal work **inside `data-boar/`**: **`Glob`**, **`Grep`**, **`SemanticSearch`** ‚Äî they respect workspace scope and avoid leaking unrelated paths into the transcript ‚Äî **unless** the operator or task clearly needs **Everything** (huge tree, path outside workspace, index speed).

## Fallback (if `es.exe` unavailable, timeout, or catastrophic failure)

1. Re-run **`.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Query "..." -FallbackPowerShell`** (same scope; **no** `-Regex`/`-Global` with fallback).
2. **`Glob`** in the workspace for **in-repo** filename patterns.
3. **`Get-ChildItem -Recurse`** only under a **narrow** root the user specified (high token/IO cost ‚Äî last resort).
4. **Never** use **`SemanticSearch`** as the primary way to locate a file **by name**.
5. **lab-op (Linux):** **`find`**, **`fd`**, **`locate`** ‚Äî **not** `es.exe`.

## When not to use

- **Content search** inside files: use **`Grep`** / **`SemanticSearch`**, not `es` (Everything is **not** full-text by default).
- **Default** project navigation: **`Glob`** for known patterns under the repo root.

## How (wrapper)

From the repo root:

| Goal | Example |
| --- | --- |
| Names under this repo (default scope), capped | `.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Query "*.md" -MaxCount 40` |
| Full index (still capped) | `.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Query "foo" -Global -MaxCount 30` |
| Custom root | `.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Query "bar" -SearchRoot "D:\work"` |
| Count only | `.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Query "*.py" -GetResultCount` |
| Show resolved invocation (copy/paste to extend raw `es`) | `.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Query "*.py" -ShowCommand` |
| Built-in usage | `.\scripts\es-find.ps1 -Help` |

**Prerequisites:** [Everything](https://www.voidtools.com/) running; `es.exe` on `PATH` or WinGet shim under `%LOCALAPPDATA%\Microsoft\WinGet\Links\es.exe`.

**Operator guide (primary Windows dev PC + lab context):** **`docs/ops/EVERYTHING_ES_PRIMARY_WINDOWS_DEV_LAB.md`**.

## Session keyword

- **`es-find`** in **`.cursor/rules/session-mode-keywords.mdc`** ‚Äî run the wrapper with a **low** `-MaxCount` unless the operator asked for an exhaustive list.

## Token hygiene

- **Always** pass a **sensible `-MaxCount`** (script default is **50**). Raise only when the operator asked for exhaustive lists.
- **Do not** paste **long** result lists into chat; summarize or take **top N** paths.
- **PII / paths:** treat `es` output like any filesystem listing ‚Äî **no** real home paths or third-party identifiers in **commits, PRs, or tracked docs** (see **`private-pii-never-public.mdc`**).
- **primary Windows dev PC:** `es-find.ps1` is **read-only** (filename index) ‚Äî safe on the primary dev workstation; it is **not** a destructive repo op (**`primary-windows-workstation-protected-no-destructive-repo-ops.mdc`**).

